# Secrets — NEVER commit
.env
**/.env
!**/.env.example

# Dependencies
node_modules/
**/node_modules/
package-lock.json

# Reorg leftovers
_to_delete/
**/_to_delete/

# Old scratch (abandoned Z-API approach)
_deprecated_zapi_scaffold/

# Self-learning: runtime failure reports (spool; synced to the top-level Improvements/).
# LOAD-BEARING: /opt/secretary is a symlink INTO the production git tree, so reports the
# container writes land in the live working copy. Untracked, they keep `git pull --ff-only`
# on the droplet unblocked and keep private chat content out of the production checkout.
secretary/improvements/*.md
secretary/improvements/_synced/

# Feature-spec spool (same load-bearing reason as improvements/ above): the skill writes specs
# here at runtime, they are pulled to the top-level New Features Plans/, and are kept out of the
# production checkout so `git pull --ff-only` on the droplet stays unblocked.
secretary/specs/*.md
secretary/specs/_synced/

# OS / editor cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
